<TITLE> Lankans due in city on Thursday </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 17 (bdnews24.com)  The Sri Lanka national cricket team are scheduled to arrive here on Thursday to play a two-test series against hosts Bangladesh as well as a tri-nation one-day international Cup. The Lankans will have practice from Friday and attend an official press conference at Sher-e-Bangla National Stadium, which will host the first Test on Dec 26-31. It will be the second full tour in Bangladesh for Sri Lanka, who had first full tour in Bangladesh in early 2006 to play a two-Test and three ODI series in Chittagong and Bogra. Before facing Tigers in the first Test, visitors Sri Lanka will play a three-day warm-up match on Dec 21. The second and final Test will be held in Chittaong from Jan 3 to 6. The tri-nation ODI series involving Sri Lanka, Bangladesh and Zimbabwe will get underway on Jan 10 with hosts taking on Zimbabwe at SBNS in Mirpur. Zimbabwe are scheduled to arrive here on Jan 4 and travel to Bogra on the same day to play two three-dayers against GP-BCB Cricket Academy side. Zimbabwe will also play a three ODI series against Bangladesh. Sri Lanka Test squad: Mahela Jayawardene (captain), Kumar Sangakkara (vice captain), Malintha Warnapura, Michael Vandort, Thilan Samaraweera, TM Dilshan, Prasanna Jayawardane, Chaminda Vaas, Muttiah Muralidaran, Dhammika Prasad, Chamara Kapugedera, Farveez Maharoof, Dilhara Fernando, Thilina Thushara Mirando and Rangana Herath. Officials: Jayantha Paranathala (manager), Trevor Bayliss (coach), Paul Farbrace (assistant coach), Ranjith Nanayakkarawasam (physiotherapist), Jade Roberts (trainer), Nalin De Alwis (computer analyst), Lal Thamel (masseur) and Guy De Alwis (IC member on tour). bd
